Day 1
1.       run a port scan on the localhost to check the status of port 80 by using the nmap command.
         nmap -p 80 localhost
 
2.       Repeat the port scan and redirect the Nmap output to a file named /nmap.first.
         sudo nmap -p 80 localhost -oN /nmap
 
3.       Display the firewall settings by using the firewall-cmd command.
         sudo firewall-cmd --list-all
 
4.       Display the firewall settings again and redirect the output to a file named /firewall.list.
         sudo firewall-cmd --list-all > /firewall.list
 
5.       Configure the firewall to allow port 80 by using the firewall-cmd command-make sure the settings are permanent and apply to the public zone.
         sudo firewall-cmd --zone=public --add-port=80/tcp –permanent
         sudo firewall-cmd –reload
 
6.       Start the Apache httpd web service by using the systemctl command.
         sudo systemctl start httpd
 
7.       Display the path to the index.html file beginning with the /var directory to check whether the Apache configuration file provides the correct path to the file by using the cd and ls commands.
         cd /var/www
         ls
 
8.       Correct the /etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf configuration file by using the nano text editor.
         sudo nano /etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf
 
9.       Start and enable the Apache
         httpd web service by using the
         systemctl command.
         sudo systemctl start httpd
         sudo systemctl enable httpd
 
10.   Display the localhost website in the Firefox web browser by using the firefox command.
         firefox http://localhost



Day 2

11.  Granting the rw permission to the user, and r to the group and other identities to the file by using the chmod command
         chmod 644 <file-name or file-path>

12.  For downloading index.html page of this site - http://localhost/
         wget http://localhost/index.html


Day 4

To run nmap scan on system: (TCP scan) nmap -sT 10.140.67.23
(UDP scan) nmap -sU 10.140.67.23

Disabling the scan's ping probes via the -PN option in TCP scan: nmap -sT -PN 10.140.67.23



 
